{"key":"processedPost-6626387","value":{"id":6626387,"first":6625867,"last":6626712,"when":1172813671,"utime":"03/02/07 07:34 AM","content":"The taller the better, because you'll have more cubic inches of space inside.  You don't want a small chamber that gets CO2 saturated.  A tiny chamber will need to get fanned out much more often.  If you drill a bunch of holes for air exchange, it can be hard to keep humidity up in a small chamber.  I'd consider about 14\" to 16\" the minimum height.  You'll need room in the bottom for your damp perlite.<br />RR","title":"Re: Does the height of my fruiting chamber matter?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}